The paper discusses a framework for online meta-learning, which involves extracting prior knowledge from existing tasks for fast learning of future tasks in a sequential setting. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), and control systems (cs.SY). Given that the paper focuses on the theoretical and empirical analysis of the proposed framework, it is most likely to be classified under cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.SY.
